Vert, 3 fesses wavy argent between 3 cinqfoils Or.

coupé au 1) de gueules à la croix estrez d’or chargée d’une croix de gueules, le montant déporté vers dextre, cantonnée en chef à dextre de deux léopards aussi d’or l’un sur l’autre, au 2) d’argent au pont droit de deux arches d’or° sur une riviére d’azur mouvant de la pointe, aux berges de sinople.

Quarterly : 1 & 4 Azur, a saltire engrailed Or between 4 bezants; 2 & 3 Argent, 3 hearts gules. The blazon of quarters 2 & 3 is that of the family de La Cour de Balleroy (extinct), former marquis de Balleroy.

taillé : au premier de gueules aux deux léopards d'or passant l'un sur l'autre senestrés d'une croix de guerre au naturel pendant du bord du chef, au second d'azur semé de vaguelettes d'argent au fer à cheval renversé d'or brochant sur le tout ; à la barre d'argent chargée de l'inscription BARON en lettres capitales de sable, brochant sur la partition.

D'argent à la cotice de gueules chargée de quatre poteries de Bavent d'or (un pot à deux anses, un broc, un vase et un pot à col évasé) posées en barre, et accompagnée en chef de trois fleurs de jonquilles aussi d'or ordonnées en orle et en pointe d'un héron contourné du même becqué et membré de sable ; au chef d'or chargé de l'inscription en capitales de sable BAVENT senestré de gueules chargé de deux léopards aussi d'or l'un sur l'autre

Argent, a cotice gules charged with 4 Bavent pots (1 with 2 handles, a pitcher???, a vase and a pot with a wide neck), all between, in chief 3 jonquil flowers in orle, and in base a heron contourny Or, beaked and membered sable; and on a chief Or, the name BAVERT in capital letters sable and ???on a sinister canton gules 2 leopards Or. (The strange division of the chief is, I believe, not blazonable in English accurately.)
De gueules au léopard accompagné en chef d'un B à dextre et d'un X à senestre, tous d'or. (confirmé en 1809)
Gules, a leopard Or, in dexter canton a B and in sinister canton an X of the second.
D'argent semé de billettes de gueules, au lion du même brochant sur le tout.
d'or au lion de sinople, armé et lampassé de gueules, couronné d'argent.
Or, a lion vert armed and langued gules, crowned argent.

parti : au premier d'azur aux trois coquilles d'argent rangées en pal, au second de sinople au château de deux tours couvertes d'argent ; à la vergette de gueules brochant sur la partition ; le tout sommé d'un chef de gueules chargé de deux léopards d'or.
Per pale azure and vert, a palet gules between to dexter 3 escallops and to sinister a 2-towered castle argent, and on a chef gules 2 leopards Or.
De sable au chevron d’or accompagné en chef d’un croissant d’argent à dextre et d’une étoile à six rais d’or à senestre et en pointe d’un lion du même lampassé de gueules.
Sable, a chevron or, in chief a crescent argent and a mullet or, in base a lion or langued gules.
D'azur à un voilier contourné d'argent, sur des ondes du même, surmonté de trois croisettes d'or.
Azure, a ship contourny argent, on waves of the same, in chief 3 crosses couped Or.

de gueules au chevron renversé cousu de sinople*, soutenu d'azur, déporté vers senestre, accompagné, en chef, d'un massacre de bœuf d'argent soutenu d'une coquille du même et, en pointe à dextre, d'une porte couverte en croupe, flanquée de deux échauguettes aussi couvertes, le tout cousu de sable mouvant de la pointe.
De gueules aux deux fasces d'or. Ce blason est celui de la famille d'Harcourt, anciens marquis de Beuvron (et duc à brevet).
D'or au lion de gueules, au chef d'azur chargé d'un croissant d'argent accosté de deux étoiles du champ.
Or, a lion gules, on a chief azure, a crescent argent between 2 mullets Or.

écartelé : au premier et au quatrième d'argent aux trois fleurs de lys soudées d'or ordonnées en chevron contourné, au deuxième et au troisième de sinople au sautoir ondé enté d'argent chargé d'une bande soudée d'or et d'une barre du même, la barre brochant sur la bande : sur le tout d'argent à la bisse ondoyante de sinople posée en pal.

Quarterly: 1 & 4 Argent, 3 fleurs de lys conjoined Or in chevron inverted; 2 & 3 Vert, on a saltire wavy argent a bend sinister surmounting a bend Or; overall ?on an inescutcheon? argent, a bisse wavy palewise vert. a 'bisse' is a type of French heraldic serpent.
d'azur au château de deux tours d'argent, ouvert de trois portes, posé sur une terrasse de sinople.
Azure, a two-towered castle argent, with 3 doors open, on a base vert.

Azure on a bend gules between in chief a seven pointed star argent and in base three bezants, a lion passant gardant bendwise or.
D’'argent à un arbre arraché au naturel adextré d'une tierce alésée ondée d'azur, au chef de gueules chargé d'un léopard d'or.
Argent, a tree eradicated proper, to dexter 3 bars wavy azure, and on a chief gules, a leopard Or.

De gueules au pont d'une arche cousu de sable mouvant des flancs, soutenu de trois coquilles d'argent ordonnées 2 et 1, à l'épée basse à dextre et à l'épi de blé à senestre, les deux d'or, posés en pal et brochant sur le tout. Gules, in base a rose argent, and on a chief sable 2 roses argent.

data: Toby Logan is a 28 year-old paramedic, who can read people's thoughts. This ability becomes very useful for his daily life, but the only person who knows his secret is his long-time friend Dr. Ray Mercer. After rescuing a young woman from a fiery car crash, Toby is troubled by visions of her missing son. She is traumatized and frightened by her abduction at gunpoint, so Toby is unable to get her to share any information. And as his own fears for the child's well-being increase, he realizes he's going to have to act quickly to make sense of the mental dissonance that plagues him. Solving the mystery Toby realizes his ability is not a curse but a "gift".

After bumping into a young homeless man, Toby is plagued by visions of a missing girl. Certain she's been abducted, he pursues the homeless person for insights into her whereabouts. But he gets more than he bargained for, including the distinct feeling that the homeless person might share his psychic abilities. The emotional overload inspires him to try and salvage his failed relationship with Dr Olivia Fawcett. Unfortunately, he's unable to quiet the visions and must act quickly if there's any hope of saving the young girl.

Realizing later the girl is missing, Toby and Detective Charlie Marks discover the truth of the situation which comes as shock to Lisa's mother.

In an effort to help her find out who killed her brother, Toby discovers a cover-up involving a Chinese crime boss who has been lying to police. As he collects telepathic thoughts and sorts through them, he realizes that Kim's brother was involved in human smuggling. They must act quickly before more lives are lost.

Toby and Oz are called to a hotel after a baby falls from a window. Before they have a chance to act, a mysterious teenage girl called Iris places her hands over the baby and revives it. When Toby catches up with Iris at the hotel, he gets a telepathic hit that makes him think someone might be trying to harm her. Toby's investigation reveals Iris' 'gift' may not be the faith-healing power everyone has come to know her for, but something equally amazing.

When Toby and Oz are called to the scene of a sexual assault, Toby, reading the victim's thoughts, sees a white-mask attacker. Toby reports this clue to Charlie Marks who, upon interviewing the victim, fears a suspected rapist in the area might be responsible. Charlie is convinced it is Brian Litvack, but has no evidence placing him at the crime scene. Her boss warns her to back off. Undeterred, she continues to investigate with Toby and discovers that although the most recent attack carries the signature of previous assaults, the attacker is not the likely suspect.

Toby and Oz are called to a crime scene, only to discover two victims, Wade and Wendy Lassiter, lying in a pool of blood. Toby senses someone else is present, and their teenage son, Andy Lassiter, is discovered, hiding and barely alive. Toby is overwhelmed with thoughts and voices, unsure exactly what they mean.With two dead parents and the only witness unable to speak, Charlie asks for Toby's help to use his telepathic ability to explore Andy's mind. Their investigation reveals Andy may suffer from a rare and puzzling mental condition. Charlie and Toby use this unusual circumstance to find out who may be responsible for the death of Andy's parents. Sibling rivalry reconvenes for Olivia when her aggravating sister, Jennifer, arrives in town and Olivia asks Toby and Oz to help provide a distancing barrier between them.

While eating out, Toby and Olivia discover that Oz works a second job at his parents' restaurant. Oz informs them his parents are behind on their mortgage payments and have 14 days to come up with $100,000 or they will lose everything. Aware of Toby's telepathic gift, Oz suggests Toby use it to help earn the money. After losing at a high-stakes poker game, Olivia tips Toby and Oz about a $100,000 reward for a dead missing person, Katie Stebbes, who disappeared after her husband Arthur took out a $5 million insurance policy on her. Currently serving prison time for allegedly murdering Katie, Arthur has maintained his innocence, claiming someone else set him up. With his telepathic gift and investigative resources, Toby believes he can solve Arthur's case and find his wife's body.

Toby and Oz attend an accident scene to find a victim, Ron, suffering from a head injury. Attempting to find out what happened, Toby reads his mind and sees an image of a beautiful young woman. Upon loading Ron on a stretcher, a handgun falls from the man's coat, along with a photo of a woman – the same woman in Toby's telepathic read. Ron loses consciousness and dies. With the help of Oz, Toby tracks down the woman, who turns out to be the victim's daughter, Lindsay. Lindsay asks if her father's death has anything to do with the four million dollars her father stole. Toby goes to see Charlie but ends up encountering Becker instead and reveals his thoughts concerning Ron's death. Examining a fifteen-year-old case, Charlie and Becker hope Lindsay can provide some insight into the missing loot. Toby, Charlie and Lindsay discover Ron might not have stolen the missing loot after all – but that someone else close to him did.

Toby and Oz's paramedic skills are called into question when, whilst trying to save a victim's life, they trample on a crime scene and compromise the evidence. Toby is able to read the thoughts of those giving testimony, including the victim's sister, who claims the accused, a record producer, was responsible for her sister's death. While Toby isn't convinced the victim's sister is telling everything she knows, he gets a telepathic hit from someone sitting in the courtroom gallery. Toby discovers the victim was being watched the night of the murder, and that an eyewitness could be the only hope of finding out what happened and who was responsible. Toby and Oz pick up a John Doe, whom Olivia diagnoses with Alzheimer's disease. Toby is unable to read John Doe's mind for clues to help determine his identity. But he is shocked when he discovers the man may hold a piece of the puzzle to Toby's mysterious past.

Toby takes Ray to the hospital to meet John Doe, whom Ray recognises as Frank Cardea, the man who brought Toby to Ray 20 years earlier. Due to his Alzheimer's, Frank continues to have trouble remembering, but he does tell Toby that Maya, Toby's mother, sent him. Toby is hit with a distress beacon, catching glimpses of a smashed windshield and a mysterious man, and attempts to learn more about the images in Frank's mind. When Olivia and Oz inform Toby about the mysterious man appearing at the hospital and EMS station, followed by a break-in at Ray's office and the disappearance of Toby's case files, Toby turns to Charlie for assistance, causing her death. With the mysterious man in pursuit, Toby races to decipher Frank's memories and uncover the truth about his mother.

data: Strange occurrences happen in the museum during the spies' field trip. Prehistoric creatures come alive! The spies are sent to investigate and therefore discover that an anthologist acting like a caveman who plans to return the world into the dinosaur age. The spiez get trapped in an erupting volcano and escape. Then, they hurry to their hometown to finish destroying the dinosaurs and defeating their baddie just in time to get home before their parents arrive. In the B-story, Megan thinks that their parents are having a baby girl and is jazzed that she won't be the only girl. Mission No. 712 Villain: Caveman

The All City Middle School Olympiad is about to have its yearly competition, but a week before the proceedings all the teams begin being attacked. Now the spiez must find out who is responsible for this mess while protecting their own school from the sabotage. The Spiez find out that a principal of another school has been the one behind the attacks. His school has always been last place in the competition, so he gets back by attacking other schools and turning his athletes into aggressive ones so they can win. Meanwhile, Lee stops being a father-like brother, and Tony chooses to be a waterboy when he didn't make it into any team. Mission No. 311 Villain: Principal Farley

Certain scientists have been abducted and the Spiez were sent to investigate. Clues found were beeswax and a giant bee stinger. At the same time, the young Spiez's snoopy aunt had come to their house and found Megan's diary, containing information about their everyday missions. The young Spiez find out that the kidnapper is a bee lady, with her DNA combined with bee DNA, and she's a fellow scientist to the scientists she abducted. Throughout the whole mission, the Aunt followed them and busted her niece and nephews about being spies saving the world, and she confronted them that she would tell their parents. Luckily, Jerry was able to erase her memory about her discovery before they could all go home. Mission No. 217 Villain: Victoria Brathwaite

An asteroid from outer space hits a space pod containing a supervillian, Alpha, and lands on Earth. Previously, him and his twin had created clones of themselves and created chaos all around the world (Thus given their nickname as the Chaos Twins). After Alpha and Omega capture two of the Spiez, the remaining two Spiez take the head of OOPSIE, another spy agency, into custody for questioning. At WOOHP headquarters they quickly learn that their parents were the ones who originally stopped Alpha and Omega. They bring their parents in and restore their past memories. But in the end all 6 Clarks are captured, and the 4 kids are sent into space. Alpha and Omega plan to use a machine to clone Cal and Karen and use the clones to wreak havoc on the world. Now the kids must learn how to stop their parents and find a way to outsmart Alpha and Omega if the world is to once again become safe. B-Story: Tami becomes best friends with the Clarks after they save her and her new sweater, but ends up causing more trouble for them as a friend than she ever did as an enemy. Mission No. 823 Villain: The Chaos Twins (Alpha and Omega) Note: This is supposedly where season 2 takes off from after this mission. However, Mission No. 987 Operation WOOCSI and Mission No. 848 Cruisin' for a Bruisin' have higher mission numbers, indicating an error in sequencing since Operation WOOCSI and Cruisin' for a Bruisin' were aired earlier.

Slick Mick tries to escape the Spiez and then is stopped by Tony and his yo-yo gadget. The public saw him stop Slick Mick and started to call him "Yo-yo Boy." Tony then gets caught up in the fame and popularity, even with Tami being the president of his fan club! The Spiez are unable to stop Slick Mick again without Tony to help, as he skips out on missions frequently. Now, the Spiez have to get Tony to forget about the fame, which he says turned out to be a 24hr job and doesn't want to do it anymore and stop Slick Mick from sending WOOHP HQ into the local lake at the same time! In the b-story, Lee must get his act back together after a humiliatingly loss of a basketball game in front of the whole school. Mission No. 726 Villain: Slick Mick (4 times!). Note: This is the produced season finale of season 1. At the end of the episode, before Lee caught Tami, Marc's eye color changed from Green like Tony and Megan, back to Hazel
